This paper deals with control strategies for a specific type of system, namely monotone systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an approach based on constraint programming, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of control actions and the focus on safety also suggest that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper applies the proposed approach to a traffic network, which falls under the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and the focus on finding control strategies suggest that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
